<paragraph id="F311E23DD5402F1C1C99FD9B432FFDA9" blockId="18.[212,311,581,605]" box="[212,311,581,605]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1C99FD9B432FFDA9" box="[212,311,581,605]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F311E23DD5402F1C1C99FDB34365FCD1" blockId="18.[212,1172,621,805]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1C99FDB34381FD71" authority="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista, 2010" authorityName="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista" authorityYear="2010" box="[212,409,621,645]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1C99FDB34381FD71" box="[212,409,621,645]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Membracis luizae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="DAE98354D5402F1C1DEDFDB343E1FD70" box="[416,505,621,644]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1EC6FDB34147FD71" authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" box="[651,863,621,645]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimica">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1EC6FDB3411CFD71" box="[651,772,621,645]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">M. mimica</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
in nearly all aspects. It differs, however, in having narrower yellow bands, especially the middle spot, the shape of which can vary among specimens. It is very small or absent in almost all examined specimens, but occasionally it can be a little larger, roughly shaped, extended for a short distance towards the inferior margin (
<figureCitation id="6B95FEB8D5402F1C1FCFFD33463EFCF1" box="[898,1062,749,773]" captionStart="Figures 16–23" captionStartId="13.[144,220,1522,1544]" captionText="Figures 16–23. Membracis species, lateral view. (16) M. flavofasciata Sakakibara (holotype 3, DZUP), junior synonym of M. celsa Walker; (17) Membracis fusifera Walker (lectotype ♀, BMNH); (18) M. latifasciata Sakakibara and Evangelista sp. nov. (holotype 3, ZMUC); (19) M. obliquifasciata Evangelista and Sakakibara sp. nov. (holotype ♀, MNHN); (20) M. luizae Evangelista &amp; Sakakibara sp. nov. (holotype ♀, DZUP); (21–23) M. luizae sp. nov., showing white band variation on a male and two female paratypes, respectively. Note: Scale bar, 2 mm." pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Figures 21–23</figureCitation>
illustrate this variation).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F311E23DD5402F1C1C99FC8943B8FC9B" blockId="18.[212,416,855,879]" box="[212,416,855,879]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1C99FC8943B8FC9B" box="[212,416,855,879]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Host plant records</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F311E23DD5402F1C1C99FCA143E6FB83" blockId="18.[212,1172,895,1143]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">
Tropical almond, 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1DD2FCA1406FFC63" box="[415,631,895,919]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Terminalia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="catappa">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1DD2FCA1406FFC63" box="[415,631,895,919]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Terminalia catappa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1EE8FCA14156FC63" box="[677,846,895,919]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Combretaceae</taxonomicName>
). Ornamental tree originated in tropical Asia, commonly found in the municipality of João Pessoa (and in others seashore cities along Brazilian Atlantic coast), popularly known as “ 
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1FA4FC614315FC03" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">castanheira-dapraia</emphasis>
”, “ 
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1D74FC0143B7FC03" box="[313,431,991,1015]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">castanhola</emphasis>
” or “ 
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1DBAFC01407DFC03" box="[503,613,991,1015]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">sombreiro</emphasis>
”. 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1EC9FC0140E9FC03" authority="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista, 2010" authorityName="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista" authorityYear="2010" box="[644,753,991,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1EC9FC0140E9FC03" box="[644,753,991,1015]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">M. luizae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="DAE98354D5402F1C1EB7FC3E414FFC03" box="[762,855,992,1015]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is highly polyphagous and was also found in many other host plants, such as 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1F3DFC21468BFBE3" authority="Blume" authorityName="Blume" authorityYear="1856" baseAuthorityName="Linneo" box="[880,1171,1023,1047]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cannabaceae" genus="Trema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micrantha">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1F3DFC214622FBE3" box="[880,1082,1023,1047]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Trema micrantha</emphasis>
Blume
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1C96FBC14349FBC3" box="[219,337,1055,1079]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ulmaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ulmaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1D29FBC14080FBC3" authority="Moric." authorityName="Moric." box="[356,664,1055,1079]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paludosum">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1D29FBC1405BFBC3" box="[356,579,1055,1079]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Solanum paludosum</emphasis>
Moric.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1EEBFBC14132FBC3" box="[678,810,1055,1079]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Solanaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1F70FBC14648FBC3" authority="Radlk." authorityName="Radlk." box="[829,1104,1055,1079]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Cupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="revoluta">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1F70FBC141E4FBC3" box="[829,1020,1055,1079]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Cupania revoluta</emphasis>
Radlk.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1812FBC14323FBA3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapindaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1D03FBE1404BFBA3" authority="DC." authorityName="DC." box="[334,595,1087,1111]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Byrsonima" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1D03FBE14002FBA3" box="[334,538,1087,1111]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Byrsonima sericea</emphasis>
DC.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1E2FFBE14113FBA3" box="[610,779,1087,1111]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Malpighiaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1F00FBE1468CFBA3" authority="Kunth" authorityName="Kunth" box="[845,1172,1087,1111]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bowdichia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virgilioides">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1F00FBE14658FBA3" box="[845,1088,1087,1111]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Bowdichia virgilioides</emphasis>
Kunth
</taxonomicName>
(Leguminosae, 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1DCFFB8143EAFB83" box="[386,498,1119,1143]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F311E23DD5402F1C1C99FB744355FB36" blockId="18.[212,333,1194,1218]" box="[212,333,1194,1218]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1C99FB744355FB36" box="[212,333,1194,1218]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F311E23DD5402F1C1C99FB0C43C6FA9E" blockId="18.[212,1172,1234,1386]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">
This species is named in honour of Maria Luiza M. Evangelista, who resides near the location where type-specimens were collected. In northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="8BB9A2ADD5402F1C1FE2FB2C41EAFAFE" box="[943,1010,1266,1290]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Brazil</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1FB0FB2C4671FAFE" authority="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista, 2010" authorityName="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista" authorityYear="2010" box="[1021,1129,1266,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1FB0FB2C4671FAFE" box="[1021,1129,1266,1290]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">M. luizae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="DAE98354D5402F1C1839FB2D431EFADE" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is popularly known as “ 
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1E56FACC4089FADE" box="[539,657,1298,1322]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">soldadinho</emphasis>
” [“tiny trooper”/“tiny soldier”] or “ 
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1866FACC469EFADE" box="[1067,1158,1298,1322]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">viuvinha</emphasis>
” [“little widow”], names that are also attributed to other resembling 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C185AFAEC433DFA9E" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C185AFAEC468CFABE" box="[1047,1172,1330,1354]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">Membracis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, like 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5402F1C1D13FA8C43CFFA9E" box="[350,471,1362,1386]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimica">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5402F1C1D13FA8C43CFFA9E" box="[350,471,1362,1386]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2147">M. mimica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
